<h2 id="10">1. Requirement: Opening a merchant account</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To work with Sofort, you first need a <a href="https://www.sofort.com/payment/users/register" target="_blank" rel="noopener">merchant account</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>. You get information as well as login details when you open the account. Without these, the plugin cannot be set up and is not usable.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Setting up a payment method</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before you can use the Online bank transfer plugin you first have to link your merchant account with your plentymarkets system.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking the merchant account:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Plugins » Plugin set overview » [select Plugin set]</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the plugin <strong>Online bank transfer</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the plugin, go to the <strong>Configuration » Base settings</strong> menu.<br>
→ Note the explanations in <a href="#table-plugin-settings">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the Configuration key.<br>
→ You get this key during the registration process.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out further settings in the <strong>Extended settings</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
